			<ns0:name>bradnelson@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/bradnelson@google.com/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Historically, the validator build has been unstable.
Frequently the attempt to specify its dependencies in a fine-grained way results in mis-specification.

Subtle changes to gyps action attachment choices have triggered:
http://code.google.com/p/chromium/issues/detail?id=77555

In order to reduce future brittleness (both in the gyp and scons builds),
we should replace fine-grained build steps with a single python script to drive the validator build linearly.
This would also have the side benefit of increasing sharing between gyp + scons builds.
